1. a printk lib, supporting printing strings and numbers(both decimal and hex);
2. outputing to a serial port;
3. a simple working and reliable interrupt/exception handling system;
4. memory map design, protected mode;
5. setup interruption/exception
6. memory management(pmm, vmm, kmalloc, page fault...);
  6.1 Get memory map from Multiboot information;
  6.2 Initialize physical memory manager (bitmap-based free page tracking);
  6.3 Implement page frame allocation/deallocation (alloc_page/free_page);
  6.4 Setup initial page directory and page tables;
  6.5 Enable paging (set CR0.PG bit);
  6.6 Implement virtual memory manager (page table manipulation);
  6.7 Implement kmalloc/kfree for kernel heap;
  6.8 Add memory protection and access control;
7. task scheduling
  7.1 Setup TSS (Task State Segment) for x86 context switch
  7.2 Define task control block (PCB) struct: PID, state, kernel_stack, registers, context
  7.3 Implement task list management: task creation, destruction, state tracking
  7.4 Implement context switch: save/restore registers and kernel stack
  > 7.5 Implement Round-Robin scheduler with time slice (e.g., 10ms)
  > 7.6 Implement main schedule loop: pick next task, switch context
  > 7.7 Setup timer interrupt for periodic scheduling
  > 7.8 Implement sys_yield and other scheduling APIs